		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2014"></a><br><code>sle2014/paper13</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2014</a> paper:</span><br><i>Model Checking of CTL-Extended OCL Specifications</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/RobertBill.html">Robert Bill</a>, <a href="../profile/SebastianGabmeyer.html">Sebastian Gabmeyer</a>, <a href="../profile/PetraRadeljakKaufmann.html">Petra Radeljak Kaufmann</a>, <a href="../profile/MartinaSeidl.html">Martina Seidl</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_13">10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_13</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagM">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> It extends OCL with temporal operators and performs model checking of the resulting specifications.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1a.html"><span class="tagL">T1A: Design</span></a><ul><li> A key contribution is the design of a CTL-extended constraint language integrated with modeling.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It provides tool support to translate/check such specifications against models.
</li></ul></li></ul>
